President Barack Obama has proclaimed October 2015 as National Arts and Humanities Month. In his proclamation, he highlights the importance of the arts and humanities in shaping our society and encourages the American people to celebrate and participate in artistic expression. He emphasizes the power of the arts and humanities to inspire and empower young people, and calls for continued support and opportunities for them to explore their creativity. The proclamation recognizes the significant impact that the arts and humanities have had on America and reaffirms the commitment to ensuring that every American has the freedom to question, discover, and create.